**Segments**

- **Product Type:** The image-guided surgery equipment and robot-assisted surgical equipment market can be segmented by product type into image-guided surgery equipment and robot-assisted surgical equipment. Image-guided surgery equipment utilizes advanced imaging technology to guide surgeons during procedures, enhancing precision and accuracy. On the other hand, robot-assisted surgical equipment involves the use of robotic systems to assist surgeons in performing minimally invasive surgeries with improved dexterity and control.

- **Application:** In terms of application, the market can be divided into neurosurgery, orthopedic surgery, laparoscopic surgeries, and others. Neurosurgery involves intricate procedures on the brain and spine, where image guidance and robotic assistance can significantly enhance outcomes. Orthopedic surgery benefits from the precision of image-guided systems and the flexibility of robotic surgical tools. Laparoscopic surgeries, which are minimally invasive procedures performed in the abdominal region, can also benefit from these advanced technologies.

- **End-User:** The end-user segment includes hospitals, ambulatory surgical centers, and others. Hospitals are the primary end-users of image-guided surgery equipment and robot-assisted surgical equipment, given the high volume of surgeries conducted in these settings. Ambulatory surgical centers, which focus on same-day surgical procedures, are also adopting these technologies to improve patient outcomes and operational efficiency.

